# HTML Guidelines

## Structure

- Every HTML file must include a valid `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration.
- Include `<html lang="en">`, `<head>` with charset and viewport meta tags, and `<body>`.
- Use Primer CSS classes from `@primer/css` for styling instead of writing custom CSS when possible.

## Accessibility

- All `<img>` elements must have an `alt` attribute.
- Use heading elements (`<h1>`–`<h6>`) in proper hierarchical order; do not skip levels.
- Ensure interactive elements are keyboard-accessible.

## Performance

- Place `<script>` tags at the end of `<body>` or use `defer`/`async` attributes.
- Prefer linking external stylesheets over inline `<style>` blocks.
